HEADWORD: hit it off
<hw>hit it off</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To get along well together; to
be compatible; to work well together; -- of people in interactive
situations; <as>as, the new chemist <ex>hit it off</ex> immediately with
his supervisor</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hitlerian</ent>⟦br⟧
